pre-release:
  1. from `release` branch: do a branchcut - release branch with current verison (release-<current_version>)
     > git checkout -b release-0.1
  2. from the new release branch, push the changes (this will create a new branch with name 'release-0.1' in remote)
     > git push origin release-0.1
  3. get back to 'release' branch
     > git checkout release
  4. update from master
     > git pull origin master
  5. run test and check if tests succeed
     > mvn clean test
  5.a If tests fail: ABORT Process and Notify
  5.b If tests pass: goto `release`

***Please note that `release-0.1` is used as an example. Replace with actual name.

release:
  1. from release branch: set correct version in pom.xml (1 + previous released version)
  2. deploy
     > ./mvnw clean deploy -P release
